init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US government appointed a young man named Brad Armstrong to lead this team.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Armstrong had great experience in the world of motorcycle racing, and was seen by officials as the perfect man to lead this team.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Armstrong's job was to locate an agency deep enough in the government to do these espionage missions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Each member is unique in their own way, but together they make a powerful force that can take on any force.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The team consisted of a biker named Crunch, an expert marksman named Bullet, and a male nurse named Poison.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: All of them were hand-picked by Armstrong and each member had a specialty they could contribute to the team.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US government had placed them undercover and in the same building as the foreign agency they would be stealing information from.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The team was able to successfully infiltrate the United Nations and steal all the files they needed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were told they did an amazing job and were now able to use this information to get the United States back into the global scene.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The team was now an integral part of the United States government and would work together with them in the future.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "The Armstrong Chronicles" is published by Image Comics.
